- in_section :imports
- content_for :header do
  %h1 Import People

.row
  .span4
    .well
      %h3 Upload File
      %p
        = render :partial => "shared/error_messages", :locals => { :target => @import }
        = raw s3_http_upload_tag :key => "imports/#{UUID.new.generate}",
            :content_type => "text/csv",
            :redirect => new_import_url,
            :acl => "public-read",
            :max_filesize => 50.megabytes,
            :submit_button => '<div class="cancel-submit"><input id="import_submit" class="btn" name="commit" type="submit" value="Import"></div>'

  .span8
    %h3 What Can I Upload?
    %p
      Please supply a CSV (comma separated values) of people that you'd like to import.
    %p You #{link_to 'download an empty CSV file', template_imports_path} with these headers already filled in.
    %p
      The first row of the file should be a row of headers specifying what each
      column represents. The list of valid column names is below. You may include
      any or all of these fields.
    %h3 Required Fields
    %table.table
      %tr 
        %td event_name
        %td The name of the event
    
    One of the three of the following is required:
    %table.table
      %tr 
        %td first_name 
        %td The first name of the patron
      %tr 
        %td last_name
        %td The last name of the patron
      %tr 
        %td email
        %td The email address of the person  
      
    %h3 Optional Fields
    %table.table
      %tr 
        %td external_customer_id
        %td A unique identifier for this customer.
      %tr 
        %td show_date
        %td The date time of the show.  We should be flexible here and accommodate many different formats with/without time too
      %tr 
        %td venue_name
        %td We're not creating a new venue object in artfully, but we can persist this somewhere.  In the order, perhaps?
      %tr 
        %td dollar_amount
        %td The dollar amount of the total purchase.  In dollars
      %tr 
        %td method_of_payment
        %td Cash, Credit Card, Check, Comp, Other.  We should be opinionated about what goes in here
